#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Apache and configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"I originally ran this straight out of my ~/public_html directory, but now we "
"have a real virtual host:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <VirtualHost *:80>\n"
"        ServerName mesh.openisp.ca\n"
"        DocumentRoot /home/mtl-mesh/public_html\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"        <Directory \"/home/mtl-mesh/public_html/\">\n"
"            Options Indexes FollowSymLinks MultiViews ExecCGI\n"
"            AllowOverride None\n"
"            Order allow,deny\n"
"            Allow from all\n"
"            AddHandler cgi-script .cgi\n"
"    \tErrorDocument 404 /ikiwiki.cgi\n"
"        </Directory>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "        Alias /repository.git /home/mtl-mesh/repository.git\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"        <Directory \"/home/mtl-mesh/repository.git\">\n"
"            AllowOverride None\n"
"            Order allow,deny\n"
"            Allow from all\n"
"        </Directory>\n"
"    </VirtualHost>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Publishing the wiki source"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"To publish the source, I use a regular HTTP server. For this, I had to "
"change the post-update hook as described [[!iki "
"todo/call_git-update-server-info_from_post-udpate_hook desc=\"here\"]], "
"which means specifically changing the git-wrapper parameter to:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "\tgit_wrapper => '/home/mtl-mesh/repository.git/hooks/post-update.ikiwiki\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "then creating the post-update hook with the following content:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    #!/bin/sh\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    ./hooks/post-update.ikiwiki\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    exec git update-server-info\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"... and setting it executable. Then the URL of the repository can be "
"published through the repolist plugin:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "\trepositories => [qw{http://mesh.openisp.ca/repository.git/}],\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The above url works because of the `Alias` directive in the above Apache "
"configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "See [[meta/Replication]] for instructions on how to replicate this wiki."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "HTTP acceleration and performance"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"First, [[ikiwiki]] is designed to serve static pages, which is very "
"efficient. Unless the wiki gets edited a **lot**, there should be no "
"performance issues hosting it. Also, the wiki emits based on the content, "
"which means that pages are cached by proxies and your browser will not fetch "
"new data until it is told so or the page changes, which is very useful. This "
"seems to be the default Apache configuration on my machine..."
msgstr ""

