#. type: Title #
#, no-wrap
msgid "Multiple committers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The [[!iki rcs/git]] page details a bit of the git internals of ikiwiki, but "
"doesn't explain clearly how to do such a setup. In order to allow multiple "
"committers, I therefore had to go through a few hoops to be able to allow "
"the web interface, myself and others to push commits to the repository."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "First, create the sandbox user:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    adduser --system --group mtl-mesh\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Those bits ensure the wrappers are suid with the group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t# group for wrappers to run in\n"
"\twrappergroup => 'mtl-mesh',\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Then the git repository (repository.git) needs to be marked as shared so "
"that permissions are kept right:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    git config core.sharedRepository group\n"
"    chmod -R g+ws .\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "To allow users to push to the repository, use:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    adduser anarcat mtl-mesh\n"
msgstr ""

